<exercise id="fs-id1172100505868">
<problem id="fs-id1172100991038">
<para id="fs-id1172100659473">Light rays fall normally on the vertical surface of the glass prism <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1.50</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> shown below. (a) What is the largest value for <m:math><m:mi>ϕ</m:mi></m:math> such that the ray is totally reflected at the slanted face? (b) Repeat the calculation of part (a) if the prism is immersed in water.</para>
