<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1172100637979">
<term>critical angle</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172100617869">incident angle that produces an angle of refraction of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>90</m:mn><m:mtext>°</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172100909883">
<term>fiber optics</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172098401232">field of study of the transmission of light down fibers of plastic or glass, applying the principle of total internal reflection</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172098314809">
<term>total internal reflection</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172098377788">phenomenon at the boundary between two media such that all the light is reflected and no refraction occurs</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
